! Key remaps for Belgian AZERTY keyboard (X11)
!
! Equivalent of the Windows AutoHotkey script.
! See the keycode table with: xmodmap -pke
!
! Format: keycode XX = normal Shift Mode_switch Mode_switch+Shift ISO_Level3(AltGr) ISO_Level3+Shift
!
! On modern X11, AltGr = ISO_Level3_Shift, which maps to column 5 (not column 3).
!
! Load:   xmodmap ~/.Xmodmap
! Most X11 desktop environments auto-load ~/.Xmodmap on login.

! AltGr + , key → < (was: U2022/bullet)
keycode  59 = semicolon period comma less less multiply

! AltGr + ; key → > (was: periodcentered)
keycode  60 = colon slash period greater greater division

! ² key → ~ (was: twosuperior)
keycode  49 = asciitilde threesuperior grave asciitilde notsign asciitilde
